strings.Value: "Sit still or I'll chop your arms and legs off!"
[Attack] "I'll deal with you once and for all!"
"Tell me, who are you and what are you doing here?"
"You'd better go back to your world. There are some fey-gobbling monsters in these lands. They'll eat you up just like that!"
"All right, let's go look at your treasures."
"I'd rather hear about your adventures."
"So what? Treasures!? I have plenty of those. You've never seen anything like the stuff I've got!"
"Go. Safe travels!"
[Attack] "Hell no! I don't forgive such behavior!"

{n}Kamala lifts the spell from the fey with a graceful gesture, and starts casting another spell to send them home. The nymph and the satyr look at you mischievously – some prank is obviously brewing in their heads.{/n}
{n}Casting fearful glances at you and your weapon, the fey sit still, waiting for the ritual to end.{/n}
"You're mean!"
"Slimeball!"
"We aren't afraid of you! We aren't – got it? Hahaha!"
{n}The fey run away, laughing out loud and sticking their tongues at you.{/n}
"I am Myrrhine and this is Kinesias. And we are bored!"
"Yeah right. We sit and talk and tell you things... As if we've nothing better to do!"

"Yes, frightfully bored! Everywhere else it's changing, flickering, like this and like that! But here it's always the same all the time! The trees don't walk, the mountains don't fly... And you're such fools! Hahaha!"
"Everything is so strange here... How do you live here at all?"
"Oh really? Monsters... Big ones? Do they have teeth?"
"Oh, really? What kind of monsters? I want to see them!"
"Let's go look for the monsters! You keep sitting here like dummies!"
"Oh, we've had such adventures – you have no idea! Beyond your wildest dreams! For instance, once we had manticore races!"
"You won't let them hurt us, will you? Will you?"
"We've been sitting here for a hundred million years! We're so bored! Let's go for a walk! We'll show you something wonderful – you'll love it!"
"And you'll be rich! You mortals love treasure, right? There you go! There's plenty of treasure around here. But without us you'll never find it your whole life!"
"You're so silly and boring! What if it's contagious? What if we become silly and boring just from sitting here with you?"
"What? Hells no! Run away before we catch it!"
"It's not far, very close... Over there!"
"Yes, they're very close... Tee-hee! Hey, did {mf|he|she} really believe that?"
"{mf|He|She} did! {mf|He|She} did! Oh, what a dummy!"
"There's not much to tell... We had some adventures! We'd just come to your world, when this mean lady decided to send us back right away!"
"Really? And what kind of treasures do you mortals have?"
"Yeah right! What would mortals know of treasures? There's probably nothing worth mentioning in your whole world!"
"Yes! Just rags, stones and scraps!"
"Show us! Show us! We want to see!"
"Another time we met the {g|LanternKing}Lantern King{/g} himself! He gave us a copper coin, half a pie and a silk stocking!"
"And one time, some hunters wandered into us! We danced with them, and we danced, and we danced until we dropped! Oh! But then we got up, and for some reason, they didn't..."
"That's it. It's time for you to go home!"
"No, no! We've only just arrived! We aren't going anywhere!" {n}The satyr takes out a pan flute and starts playing.{/n}
{n}You feel drowsy for a moment, but the spell's effects quickly clear. Realizing his spell didn't work, the satyr hides his flute.{/n} "Um... All right, we should probably go..."
{n}You feel drowsy. Your eyes close involuntarily, and you can't even move a finger.{/n}
"There's no place like home!"
